originalText.text: Great service. You are next to the Rockefeller Center, Time square etc. You arrive to P1 level. From there they either take your car or send you to P2. They are clear w the Price and very fast to get back to your car. The car is in a good space and we just return there and they were fast.  We notice very expensive cars there so we knew we can trust them. They have a bathroom on p1 for the customers which was priceless. It was our first parking there and I will park it again. I prepaid reserving the parking online. If you plan to go is better during weekdays but worth the trip and great parking place.

originalText.text: This place was great! They were pretty fast for a large and busy garage compared to others I've used. I picked up my car after 5 pm, which of course is  "Rush Hour" sooo yeah! They have multiple levels(3), so elevators are used from the street level but you can take the stairs if you prefer. After I paid, my wait time ...10 min max. I can't say you"ll experience the same, but bare in mind it is located in mid town Manhattan. So folks, FYI, the best and least expensive way to pay for garage parking in New York is to use a "Garage Parking Ap." You can download one to your phone ... Google Play if you use an Android or the Apple store for you lovers of all things Apple. Set it up with your payment of choice, credit card, bank, paypal, etc. and you're  good to go. It's  quick and convenient because you can search for a parking garage area close to your destination and find the best discounted pricing. I paid $29 bucks for 12 hours!! I personally use the "Best Parking" application. Do your research!
